    <Notice Locale="UK">
        <Text><![CDATA[
※ Please update in an environment where the Bluetooth connection is most stable.
※Update may be unavailable if a Bluetooth Low Energy device (wearable device, smartwatch, etc.) is connected to the Android device (or iOS device). Perform update after disconnecting all Bluetooth devices other than this device from the Android device (or iOS device).
※ Please be careful not to update while in riding on vehicles, such as trains, or in environments where 2.4 GHz band radio waves such as Wi-Fi, microwave ovens, cordless phones and many other radio waves are intermingled.

※ Sony | Headphones Connect ※
Please update to the latest version before updating the main unit

[Update details in version 3.0.5]
[1] Now supports the beta version of LE Audio that is optimal for games, etc.
  - Xperia 1 Ⅳ/Xperia 5 Ⅳ is required (use the latest version of smartphone software).
[2] Quick Access settings for Ximalaya are now easier to configure.

This update includes update content that had previously been applied to this model.

[Notes]
1) Software update takes about 40 minutes for Android or about 60 minutes for iOS.
This product continues to function as headphones even while downloading updates and transferring data. If the update fails, stop playing the music and try updating again.
2)Perform update after confirming that the remaining battery charge is sufficient on the headphones and Android device (or iOS device).
3)Set the "Automatic Power Off" function (power off function when non-equipped) of "Sony | Headphones Connect" to "Do not turn off" when updating while LinkBuds S is unequipped. 
*If settings had been changed for the update, be sure to restore the settings to the former settings after update is complete.

[How to check the software version]
Select [LinkBuds S Version] from the upper right menu of Sony | Headphones Connect application screen. 


